{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_49","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2`. Preserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-2719-library-new-request-xerces-xmlParserAPIs-2.6.2-86c7b7be\n\nThe most likely failing stage was post-generation review/finalization, not raw Gradle validation. In the preserved worktree, `checkstyle` passed (`human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-02T00-32-18-215759Z.log`), and the saved Gradle outputs under `build/tests/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/` show `test`, `nativeTestCompile`, `nativeTest`, and `generateDynamicAccessReport` succeeding. However, the generated patch is not acceptable for a `library-new-request`: relative to `origin/master` it modifies shared harness code in `tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSupport.java`, and the generation log explicitly says this was done because the dynamic-access report contained `Unknown Source` frames with no line numbers, so the agent changed the reporter to fall back to JaCoCo method coverage. The run also adds legacy test-only native-image config files at `tests/src/xerces/xmlParserAPIs/2.6.2/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/xml-parser-apis-tests-only/reflect-config.json` and `.../resource-config.json`, which are not acceptable for new-library submissions. The metrics file still records the run as `failure` after 11 iterations and 992 generated LOC, despite 12/12 dynamic-access coverage.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-07-31-007803Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-02T00-29-32-866009Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/xerces:xmlParserAPIs:2.6.2/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-